Shiraz Nawaz said he felt lucky to be alive after the 15-foot flames shot out of the manhole in the West Midlands . 
  The 36-year-old was walking to his local takeaway when he heard buzzing from the ground just a few feet behind him . 
  Thick black smoke then erupted from the cover in Shirley, Solihull just moments after he had walked over it . 
  Mr Nawaz managed to grab his phone in time to film the terrifying incident . 
  Firefighters said the blaze was caused by an electrical fire in an underground link box . 
 